40:27.800 --> 40:29.680
the cutting edge of medicine.

40:29.680 --> 40:33.520
It's at BG. What are you doing with
that cigarette? Don't you read?

40:33.520 --> 40:37.040
There is a greater death
rate among people who smoke.

40:37.040 --> 40:40.120
No, I don't think I could leave
St Eligius, Mark, I really don't.

40:40.120 --> 40:42.640
I feel a connection here with
the people, the neighbourhood.

40:42.640 --> 40:45.360
Hey, I'm happy that you have
a deep and abiding affection

40:45.360 --> 40:47.680
for this slaughter house
and all these sleaze bags.

40:47.680 --> 40:49.440
But not me.

40:49.440 --> 40:52.040
Good luck with
             your career, Westfall.

40:52.040 --> 40:53.520
Better tell Dominion you're leaving.

40:53.520 --> 40:57.520
Better tell Dominion you're leaving.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

41:09.520 --> 41:12.520
Oh, Craig.
Just dropped in on Mr Kellogg.

41:12.520 --> 41:14.320
He's doing well.
You should be pleased.

41:14.320 --> 41:14.680
Thank you, sir.

41:14.680 --> 41:18.040
Thank you, sir.
You wouldn't happen to know where
my Gabaudy mitral valvular tome is?

41:18.040 --> 41:20.480
No, sir.

41:20.480 --> 41:23.520
Sir. About my coming back
           next year...

41:23.520 --> 41:27.040
I'm looking forward to it.
God knows why.

41:27.040 --> 41:31.040
Yeah, me too, sir.

41:44.280 --> 41:46.080
MICROPHONE ECHOES

41:46.080 --> 41:50.080
Is it working?

41:50.080 --> 41:51.760
      Wait a minute, Donald.

41:51.760 --> 41:53.520
         Listen, everyone.

41:53.520 --> 41:55.200
            Quiet down.

41:55.200 --> 41:57.760
             Hey, you!

41:57.760 --> 42:00.000
             Shut up!

42:00.000 --> 42:02.240
             Go ahead.

42:02.240 --> 42:05.600
Well.

42:05.600 --> 42:08.080
Here we are.

42:08.080 --> 42:10.160
Looking at the past,

42:10.160 --> 42:11.760
thinking of the future.

42:11.760 --> 42:15.600
And, like it or not,
we have to face our feelings

42:15.600 --> 42:19.000
and mistakes and our shortcomings.

42:19.000 --> 42:21.720
God knows we've seen enough pain

42:21.720 --> 42:23.680
and death.

42:23.680 --> 42:25.560
So I suppose we should be depressed.

42:25.560 --> 42:28.520
But because this building stands
here, and because of the people

42:28.520 --> 42:30.840
who have walked through that door,

42:30.840 --> 42:34.840
the human spirit prospers,
    and moves on.

42:35.200 --> 42:38.840
You know, it wasn't long ago that,
if a man came in here with

42:38.840 --> 42:41.600
a dying heart,
all we could offer was solace.

42:41.600 --> 42:45.600
And now we can offer a transplant.

42:46.360 --> 42:49.400
And that, to me, is amazing.

42:49.400 --> 42:53.080
They call us a teaching hospital.

42:53.080 --> 42:55.400
But I find this a learning place.

42:55.400 --> 42:59.400
And whether it be nurses or
orderlies or surgeons, or patients,

43:01.160 --> 43:03.840
we all have something
to offer each other.

43:03.840 --> 43:06.320
And I want to salute those
people who have brought us

43:06.320 --> 43:10.320
to this celebration, and to those
who will lead us in the future.

43:11.280 --> 43:15.280
Daniel?

43:21.200 --> 43:24.720
Happy birthday, St Eligius.

43:24.720 --> 43:25.640
To the future!

43:25.640 --> 43:29.640
To the future!
To the future!

43:36.120 --> 43:38.640
                 How's the new cast?

43:38.640 --> 43:40.080
Fine.

43:40.080 --> 43:43.400
Jack, look!

43:43.400 --> 43:47.400
Oh!

43:53.920 --> 43:55.800
Hiya, buddy.

43:55.800 --> 43:59.800
              Daddy.

44:44.440 --> 44:46.720
Quite a hospital
you've built, Father.

44:46.720 --> 44:48.600
Well, it's God's design to be sure.

44:48.600 --> 44:51.040
Since he never went
to architecture school, I had

44:51.040 --> 44:53.080
 to draw up the blueprints myself.

44:53.080 --> 44:57.080
Let's see you hit Flannery's
pub across the street.

44:58.320 --> 45:35.000
             'Got it!'
